<div class="body" id="fhbody-174692124">
	
		
	

	
		
		<div id="text-174692124" class="p">
			
		 	
				Disney Plus will soon <a href="https://www.theverge.com/2024/8/7/24215224/disney-password-sharing-crackdown-september">no longer let you share your password</a> with people outside your household. From a report:<i> During an earnings call on Wednesday, Disney CEO Bob Iger said the crackdown will kick off "in earnest" this September. The timeline for Disney's password-sharing crackdown has been a bit confusing so far. In February, Disney announced plans to roll out paid sharing and also began notifying users about the change. It then launched paid sharing in a "few countries" in June but provided no information on when it would reach the US.</i><br>
		 	
		</div>

		

		

		
			
		
	</div>
